ENTRY            14719   20260127   20260316   20260316       1526
SUBENT        14719001   20260127   20260316   20260316       1526
BIB                 16         36
TITLE      Cross Sections for Neutron Production from 6- and
           10-MeV Neutrons Incident on 10B and 11B
AUTHOR     (P.W.Lisowski,M.Drosg,D.M.Drake,B.Hoop)
INSTITUTE  (1USALAS,2AUSVIE)
           (1USAUSA) Harvard Medical School,Boston,Massachusetts
REFERENCE  (J,NSE,195,1131,2021)
           #doi:10.1080/00295639.2021.1906588
REL-REF    (O,12986001,M.Drosg+,R,LA-10665-MS,1986)
           Previous analysis.
FACILITY   (VDGT,1USALAS) Experiment performed at the pulsed
           tandem Van de Graaff accelerator at the Los Alamos
           National Laboratory
DETECTOR   (SCIN) The detector was an NE-213 liquid scintillator
           with 12 cm in diameter and effective thickness of 3
           cm. It was in direct contact with the face of an
           RCA-8854 photomultiplier.
METHOD     (TOF)
MONITOR    (1-H-1(N,EL)1-H-1,,SIG)
MONIT-REF  (,J.C.Hopkins+,J,ND/A,9,137,1971)
INC-SOURCE (P-T) Neutrons were produced by the 1H(t,n)3He
           reaction. The target was a gas cell with an entrance
           foil of 5.3 mg/cm2 of molybdenum and a beam stop of
           0.05 cm of gold. Irradiation were performed at 0 deg.
ANALYSIS   Normalized net time spectra were converted to energy
           spectra using first order relativistic approximation.
CORRECTION Multiple scattering correction was made using using
           Monte Carlo MCNP 6.2 code.
ERR-ANALYS The uncertainty in incoming beam direction was 0.4 deg.
           (ERR-2,,0.5) Systematic uncertainty in monitor mass
           (ERR-3) Systematic uncertainty in monitor cross section
           (ERR-6,,0.5) Systematic uncertainty in normalization
STATUS     (APRVD) Approved by P.W.Lisowski on January 28, 2026.
HISTORY    (20211102C) Compiled by S.H.
           (20260311A) BP: Replaced digitized with the tabulated
                      data in sub 14-15, added DOI, REL-REF, added
                       subentries 16-17.
ENDBIB              36
COMMON               2          3
ANG-ERR    ERR-3
ADEG       PER-CENT
        0.1         1.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           43
SUBENT        14719002   20260127   20260316   20260316       1526
BIB                  7         21
REACTION   (5-B-10(N,EL)5-B-10,,DA)
REL-REF    (R,13162001,E.T.Sadowski+,J,PR/C,42,190,1990)
SAMPLE     (5-B-10,ENR=0.955) Irregularly shaped cylinder
           of approximately 1.7 cm diameter and 4 cm height with
           a mass of 1.80 mol.
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-T) Total uncertainty
           (ERR-4) Uncertainty in correction for multiple
                   scattering
           (ERR-7) Syst. uncertainty in Monte Carlo correction
           (ERR-S) Combines statistical uncertainty, in dead time
                   correction and background subtraction
CORRECTION In the case of 10B at 6 MeV, neutrons from the first
           excited state at 0.719 MeV (n,n1) could not be
           confidently separated from the elastic scattering
           peak at forward angles. The authors therefore used a
           Legendre polynomial fit to the data of E.T.Sadowski
           et al. combined with our back-angle data to generate
           a correction to the sum over the elastic and first
           inelastic states.
STATUS     (CURVE,,P.W.Lisowski+,J,NSE,195,1131,2021) Fig. - 4
HISTORY    (20260115A) BP: Updated STATUS, added CORRECTION.
ENDBIB              21
