       27.5   2.26E+02
       38.3   1.41E+02
       49.1   8.21E+01
       65.1   2.97E+01
       80.8   2.88E+01
       96.1   4.36E+01
      115.6   4.93E+01   2.34E+00
      134.6   4.35E+01   2.06E+00
      148.5   4.69E+01   2.48E+00
ENDDATA             12
ENDSUBENT           42
SUBENT        14719003   20260127   20260316   20260316       1526
BIB                  6         20
REACTION   (5-B-10(N,EL)5-B-10,,DA)
SAMPLE     (5-B-10,ENR=0.955) Irregularly shaped cylinder
           of approximately 1.7 cm diameter and 4 cm height with
           a mass of 1.80 mol.
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-T) Total uncertainty
           (ERR-4) Uncertainty in correction for multiple
                   scattering
           (ERR-7) Syst. uncertainty in Monte Carlo correction
           (ERR-S) Combines statistical uncertainty, in dead time
                   correction and background subtraction
CORRECTION At 10 MeV, the authors summed the double differential
           cross section over both states and used the
           ENDF/B-VIII evaluated data for the first excited
           state as a correction. An estimated uncertainty of
           25% of the subtracted inelastic cross-section value
           was combined quadratically with the experimental
           statistical uncertainty to take into account the
           uncertainty in the data used to make the correction.
STATUS     (CURVE,,P.W.Lisowski+,J,NSE,195,1131,2021) Fig. - 4
HISTORY    (20260115A) BP: Updated STATUS, added CORRECTION.
